  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Post CE mark ICD patients eligible for implantation of the S-ICD system
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria

          1. Age &gt;/= 18yrs

          2. Eligible for implantation of an S-ICD system per local clinical guidelines or
             currently implanted with an S-ICD system (SW version 1.59.0 or later)

          3. Willing and able to provide written informed consent or have informed consent as
             provided by a legal representative

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. 1. Participation in any other investigational study that may interfere with
             interpretation of the Registry results

          2. Incessant ventricular tachycardia and/or spontaneous, frequently recurring
             ventricular tachycardia that is reliably terminated with anti-tachycardia pacing

          3. Patients with unipolar pacemakers or implanted devices that revert to unipolar pacing
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
